## 3. Deploy Windows LAPS to Kill Shared Local Admin Passwords
 
Identical local `Administrator` passwords across machines are the single biggest lateral-movement enabler. **Windows LAPS v2** (built into Server 2019+) rotates each machine's local admin password and stores it encrypted in AD.
 
```powershell
# Extend the AD schema (run once, as Schema Admin)
Update-LapsADSchema
 
# Grant computers the right to write their managed password
Set-LapsADComputerSelfPermission -Identity "OU=Servers,DC=corp,DC=local"
```
 
Then enable the LAPS policy via GPO and set password complexity + rotation age (30 days is a reasonable default). I wrote a full walkthrough in the [Windows LAPS v2 lab](/posts/) if you want the step-by-step.
 
