## Verification: Prove It Actually Applied
 
Hardening you didn't verify is hardening you don't have. After deployment:
 
1. Run **`gpresult /h report.html`** on a target server to confirm the GPOs applied.
2. Use **Microsoft Policy Analyzer** to diff live config against the baseline.
3. Re-scan with a tool like **PingCastle** (for AD) to score your domain and catch what you missed.
---
 
## Closing
 
None of these are exotic. They're the boring, high-leverage controls that turn a single compromised endpoint into a dead end instead of a domain takeover. Start with the baseline, layer LSA Protection and LAPS to protect credentials, cut NTLM/SMBv1/unsigned-LDAP, lock down RDP, and enforce tiering so your admin credentials never end up somewhere they can be stolen.
 
Pick two items this week. Pilot them. Verify. Then do two more.
 
